The paper deals with privacy and security in distributed hash tables (DHTs), which are commonly used in peer-to-peer networks. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves algorithms and data structures for DHTs (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and network infrastructure (cs.NI).
